DialogueText: Ah, greetings new recruit! I’m Professor N. It’s nice to mee-
OH NO!! THE BOOKS!!! THEY’RE FALLING!!!
Where was I? Yes, that’s right! Welcome to the Command Deck! This is where you will receive missions. As a new recruit, you must forge a Biobot of your own before you begin your training.

Biobots are living robots that grow  in different ways, based on their human. For example, my Biobot, T.O.G.A, has grown an extra pair of strong arms to help carry huge stacks of research books with me. With a bit of training, you and your Biobot will make the perfect team!

Biobot training of course! You’re here because you show great potential to join an elite rescue force of humans and Biobots known as the Bioknights. There’s only one way to find out if that’s true. Train a Biobot here at the academy and show us what you’ve got.
What do you think? Ready to create your Biobot and begin your training?
Option2: Could you tell me about Biobots again?
Option3: Could you tell me about training again?

DialogueText: To create the best Biobot for you, you will need to feed the generator with some information about you.
Let’s start with your talents/skills/strengths. What three things on this list do you think you are good at?
Choose 3 talents from the list below or write your own in the “Other” box.
Wow! I’m impressed! You have some useful skills great strengths there!
Could you tell me some things about yourself? Your answers will decide which Biobot you’ll create.
Lastly, in front of you are three Biocrystals. They are what gives Biobots life. Choose whichever one you like to form the heart of your Biobot.
Interesting choice!! Now, place it into the Generator to create notch to create your very own Biobot!
Allow me to introduce you to…
Hey!! Don’t I know you? Yeah it IS you!!
Option1: Wait a minute, your voice is kind of familiar. Have we played a game online or something? Wait.. PRINCESSPEACH217!!?
Option2: Yeah, you look kind of familiar. Didn’t we go to the same school on Earth? You’re the leader of the soccer team right?
Option3: Yeah, I think I’ve seen you before. Don’t we live on the same street on Earth? You’re the one with that big dog that always barks when I walk past. You’re the girl who owns all those dogs right? What do you have, like, 6 now?

DialogueText: That’s right!! I’m Tyra. I can’t believe we BOTH got recruited! It’s nice to see a familiar face!
OH NO YOU DIDN’T!!!!
OH NO I DID!!! What have I done!!?
YOU’VE TOTALLY RUINED MY OUTFIT!!!
S-sorry! I just -
SORRY!? You did that on purpose!
Hey! What’s going on?
This kid just barged into me and my Biobot!
....Is that all?
ANNNND he dumped his stinky sticky space juice all over my new outfit! It’s in my hair too!! GROSS!!!
Ok yikes! Wait. What? Wait a minute..
What!?
Is it really called “Space Juice” oh yeah it is. Wow... so... creative…
Forget about what it’s called! It’s ALL OVER ME!!!
Oh no! I’m so sorry! I was just trying to find my class and I’m completely lost!
Easy to be lost if you’re not watching where you’re going! Besides, your map is upside down, genius.
I think... What Atlas is trying to say is “it’s not safe to walk around this busy courtyard with your head in a map.”
Don’t worry, errr. What’s your name?
It’s Zac.
Right, don’t worry Zac. Atlas is just mad cos you melted his hair wax.
Wow. Okay. I thought we were friends Ty! Why are you on this guy’s side??! Plus.. it’s not wax….
It's Styling Gel.
Uhuh… sure. Well you’ve got ‘styling gel’ running down your face, tough guy.
Don’t worry! I got your back Atlas! Zac better watch where he’s going next time.
Thank you, new kid! See!? Now there’s the support I needed from you, Ty!
Jeez. Always so dramatic..
Okay, okay, sorry! I’ll be more careful next time…
Good!
Great! We better get to class now! We’re all super late!
Hey! What about the space juice!?? I’m still completely soaked!
You’re right… We better run fast so you can dry out on the way. Hahaha!
NOT FUNNY!!!
I think Zac just needs some help. We’re all new here!
(to Zac) Hey, it’s alright, Atlas can see that you’re very sorry…
What?!
(to Atlas) Hey it was just an accident, why don’t we calm down. I’ll help you out with those stains.... I packed an extra shirt. You can wear it if you want.
Ugh… I guess that would work for now…
Thanks……... sorry about that!
Are you sorry though?
YES!!! Of course I am!
I’m just messin with you!
WE KNOW!!
I think Tyra’s right.
Right!? Great minds think alike!
You need to calm down, Atlas. Zac said sorry like a million times.
Sor...
WE KNOW!!
Well can your great minds figure out how to remove space juice stains from my uniform before we’re all late to class?
You’re right… We better run fast so you can dry out on the way. Hahaha!
NOT FUNNY!!!

Welcome to Mechology - the study of Biobots! Today we are learning to identify the parts of a Biobot. To be a great team, a Bioknight and their Biobot must know each other - inside and out. So why don’t we start with the most important part of a Biobot?
Who can tell me what gives a Biobot life?
Oh, is it... the Biocrystal?
That’s right!
But for extra points, how many colours of Biocrystal are there?
Three... I think.
Three! And they are..?
Blue, Red and Purple.
Well done!
Pshhh! Put your hand down, you cheater.
Atlas! What are you talking about!?
Don’t you know?
Know what?
There was a glitch in the Academy system this year... Apparently one student isn’t meant to be here, and I reckon it’s them!
What!? No way! We used to be neighbors.
What!? No way! We used to go to the same school!
What!? No way! We used to play Dungeon League online together!
Come on! It’s obvious!! Look at them trying to cover it up! They’re trying to answer every question. They’re trying to prove they're meant to be here so we don’t suspect them.
Did you hear what they were whispering about me before? It’s not true!
Yeah, total lies! You alright?
Not really...
This always happens! I remember a few years ago, I spilled juice on my pants, like one time, and everyone called me WIZZ KID all year! IT WAS JUST JUICE!!!
Hahaha! Wow, what is it with you and juice?! Sorry to laugh!
Hahaha! It’s okay! It’s funny now. People stopped calling me that after a while. No one calls me that anymore.
Why?
I don’t know… I guess when you don’t pay attention to rumours, people just forget about them…
Just don’t go reminding anyone, okay!?
Your secret is safe with me, Wizz Kid!
HEY!!! Hahaha!
Hey Tyra, Atlas, wait up! You’re not going anywhere!
Yeah?
I heard what you said! It’s not true! I got an invite and I can prove it.
What?
How did I cheat?
He didn’t say.
But of course you’d say you didn’t cheat. That’s what a cheater WOULD say!
Well if you actually asked me, I could show you proof. Here is the invite.
Oh...Hm.. (confused) I’m sorry… I guess we shouldn’t listen to rumours..
(should say something here)
Yes you shouldn’t! You never know if you’re hurting someone by just “talking”.
(run towards Tyra) Atlas, wait up!
Huh?
Why are you saying those ridiculous rumours?!
What are you talking-
You’re saying I’m not qualified to be in this academy!
Yeah well...
How did I cheat then?! You’re just a bunch of liars!
He didn’t say.
But of course you’d say you didn’t cheat. That’s what a cheater WOULD say!
Well if you actually asked me, I could show you proof. Here is the invite.
oh… ugh.. It was a mistake I guess!! We couldn’t have known they made that up!
Yeah don’t go calling people liars! It’s not our fault anyways!
Well then don’t go around repeating rumours! You can piss someone off real bad!
